      parentTakeaway: 'School as a research subject — share stories about your own school experiences and how they compare to your child’s experience noticing what has changed and what has stayed the same, explore together how schools work in other countries through library books, online videos, or conversations with people from different cultural backgrounds, analyze the school schedule together calculating how much time is spent on each subject and discussing why the school allocates time that way, encourage children to think critically about what makes a good learning environment and what they would change if they could, and discuss how all the different people in a school community work together to create a place where children can learn and grow.',
